{
  "texts": [
    "For the qualitative data of the research, some focus participants were invited to participate in the focus group interview at the end of the implementation.",
    "Academic achievement test The Medical English Academic Achievement Test was constructed by researchers by quoting the reading texts and exercise sections of the book Medical English Clear and Simple: A Practice-Based Approach to English for ESL Healthcare Professionals written by Hull (2010).",
    "The exercises Hull presented were reviewed by a team of education experts and a specialist physician who was a researcher in the study.",
    "The achievement test consisted of 20 multiple-choice questions about the anatomy of the digestive and nervous systems, diseases, symptoms, treatments, and topics covering the teaching of therapeutic concepts for only 4 weeks.",
    "The test was developed after applying it to the students who took this course the previous year."
  ]
}